 and Ho this and that, and all sorts of things that made me cringe as a roleplayer. I was going to stick out the whole raid til power outage fried out my pcs power supply and knocked out all the power for a few hours, that was fun. Anyway to my point I guess, is FV turning into a standard Blue server with UBERS and DOODS or is there some hope the Roleplayers are out there somewhere en masse and have all the L33t ppl on ignore. Sad seeing what the server has become. Its no wonder the population is low. Grouping is next to impossible, communications are limited, the all on /roleplay was the stupidest part of FV, the TLC worked completely ass backwards from how VI planned it here and Roleplay exists in a mild to light moderate state. <br>Ok rant off, just sad to see the dreams I fought so hard for for so many years, yes years - RPs have been trying for a RP only server since month 1 after release, get washed away because Verant decided to use this server to BETA TEST more frivolous code no one wanted. /sigh oh well guess I'll make the best of this server and ignore the L33ts or just head back to a blue server where crap is so much easier to do. BTW most of the GREAT RP ppl I met in our travels to the high end game are all gone for one of the reasons I mentioned above. I knew ppl in the top 5% in lvls on this server that dropped off at 30 and 35th lvls when they could have made a difference in how FV evolved but left for greener pastures. Guess the Verant Gods wanted another sick joke to laugh at and made FV. Not sure if I should laugh or cry because this is NOT the server they promised at the fan faire 10 months ago. <br><br>Best Wishes Anyway!!<br>Stormwind<br><br>PS - may just start a low lvl Kitty Rogue and just play in the low end game til the RPers catch up in lvls, who knows.... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormwindthunderpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormwind Thunderpaw</A> at: 12/4/01 6:18:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkus>Darkus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 6:16:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> I like this server.  Its a great server for soloing.  Play a necro, mage or druid for full enjoyment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BakoFV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 6:37:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> I dont roleplay alot, cause frankly i am not good at it, but when someone talks to me in character i try best to answer in character, and I try to sound roleplaying whenever i can. When I am around my friends who know me well, my speach tends to be non roleplay .... but with outward comunity i do try my best. this I have seen as the most kind of additude with the higher end people i am around. Always roleplay, no , try to best when the situation calls for it, yeah. <p>Bako Emberfist<BR>Iksar Monk <BR>Guild Leader of Fire and Fury <BR>Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 7:11:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> So, ya PL'd up  and you're surprised at the top ya find folks that play the game to win it and lightly roleplay on the side ?<br><br>Sorry but allot of folks that are great roleplayers haven't broken 10 yet, and they might not ever make it past that point.<br><br>Oh, and you went to an open raid situation and you're surprised that folk aren't rp'n. Raid's exist to take down big/allot of mobs and get phat l3wts. No other reason to go on them really.<br><br>Roleplay buffing stations and camping to chat &lt;snicker&gt;<br><br>There are allot of roleplayers around, there are folk that came here just to get a low population. There are folk that use this as an alt server to vent there roleplaying grief then go back to raiding.<br><br>Lotsa folk doing lots oh stuff,<br>If you have a problem with someone, thing take a look at yourself first.<br><br>Just observations<br><br>Those are my 2 pennies don't were em out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormwindthunderpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormwind Thunderpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 7:38:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> Dal uhm ... I earned everything I have and quested for. I had a regular group who played the same hours every day. In my previous post I mentioned that I knew alot of ppl that did the same and were similar lvls, most have left the server. MANY of the ones that stayed and are same lvls were corrupted by the doods and thier need for greed and gear. Fine thats thier choice so be it, it wasnt mine so don't tell me to look at myself as if I am the problem. I had alot of time to play, quest, RP and meet ppl yet still got the lvls done. The roleplayers may be casual gamers here and thats fine also. My original point was that most of the server isnt RP at all in any form and this isnt why the server was created. For a &quot;good&quot; race/class character to kill outright other good race/mobs isnt RP but it happens alot here.  Dood speak is not RP but is common in many places moreso than &quot;in character&quot; texts are. It was an observation I was having not a finger pointing session so please take the snide &quot;If you have a problem with someone, thing take a look at yourself first&quot; comments and keep them to yourself thanks!<br><br>Storm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mudslingin' Admin</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 8:20:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> Hmm, just because someone levels fast doesn't mean they are not true roleplayers.<br><br>Some of us have been playing this game for many years and find it easier to level than others. Some of us have more time to play than others, and therefore level up faster. I've taken flak for being level 32 (which is not very high, relatively speaking) -- but at 22 days /play time it's to be expected that I probably am not going to be level 10. <br><br>I have a lot of time to waste, a lot of time to roleplay, and a lot of time to level. Doesn't make me any less of a roleplayer because I have levels. <p><font face="arial" size="-1" color="green"><b>Ankles Dirtyfoot</font><font face="arial" size="-1"> <<a href="http://www.geocities.com/starspunguild">Starspun</a>><br></b><i>Black-soled, bow-slingin' hippie</i><br><a href="http://pub96.ezboard.com/fstarspun37494frm7.showMessage?topicID=5.topic">Anklebites - A Wanderer's Journal</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 9:49:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> Stormwind says : None of the 3 characters I have been playing at the same time and powerleveled to 50 plus think you all are role playing. So you better just stop it or I will leave!<br><br>Heagan : Huh? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugiordanaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GiordanaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 10:18:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> I don't judge people by their level, some people get to a high level and don't roleplay, others roleplay and get to a high level anyway, others roleplay and stay relatively low-level.  Depends on a lot of things.  If I had an easier time getting into groups (i.e. finding people to group with) I'd probably be a higher level too, not because I don't like to roleplay, but because I like to roleplay at the same time as getting experience.  For me, roleplaying is interacting in-character with whoever I'm hunting with at the time.  It doesn't mean putting leveling on hold because I'd rather roleplay; they're not mutually exclusive.  Except for when I'm spending time working on trade skills instead of levelling, but lately I'm too poor to spend much time on trade skills.<br><br>FV has been a bit of a disappointment for me.  I'm not sure what I was expecting, but I haven't really found it.  I think the TLC and language barriers have done more to discourage roleplay than to foster it.  And I think the server has become more of a haven for people who either a) prefer to solo, b) make friends easily, or c) brought their own friends or guild to the server.<br><br>I don't enjoy soloing. EQ was my first experience with a multi-player online game and when I first started I didn't think I'd ever get used to grouping with people.  Now I'm just the opposite, I don't enjoy soloing even when I play a class suitable for soloing.  I'd much rather be in a group.<br><br>But-- I'd rather just find people at random, than have to rely on a regular group of people.  I miss the freedom of walking up to the gnoll spires in South Karana and finding a group of people I've never met and saying Hey, mind if I join you guys? and either being accepted or being put on a wait list.  I don't want to just send /tells to people I've grouped with before and asking what they're doing and if I can tag along.<br><br>And no, I didn't bring friends or guildmates from my old server.  The people from my old server who knew I was leaving for FV didn't want to come to FV, partly because they anticipated the very problems I'm finding here.<br><br>I'm not really finding people to roleplay with, in groups.  It's as though grouping for exp and roleplaying are incompatible.  The other night I was in a group in High Keep and we all were speaking human, so I started speaking a bit in goblin, and the response was ????? so I explained that since no one was speaking another language, and we were killing goblins, I thought I'd give a fast lesson in goblin (I trained 1 point in it at the guild).  And someone asked me if that helped my taunt, and I said &quot;what, taunting them in Goblin? Yeah, they're so offended by the way I massacre their language they want to kill me all the more.&quot;  That, for me, is roleplaying, and it's not incompatible with grouping for exp.<br><br>Basically the problem seems to be that no one agrees on a definition of roleplaying, and people are too quick to point fingers at each other and throw around accusations.  So yeah, we're ending up with a lot of the same problems as the other servers, only there are a lot fewer of us here, and everyone knows everyone else pretty much on the board, and that's not always a good thing.<br><br>-Giò,<br>being unusually wordy on the board tonight because she can't get in to Norrath... grrr.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveloxiavoluptuous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veloxia Voluptuous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/01 10:52:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> I try to roleplay... i slip in and out of rolepllay. when i get angry, there's no way i can RP.  I do try to though, especially when others are around me.  but often i want to talk about things in game that arent in character too... as you would with RL friends.  <br>Also, i used to be somewhat of a powerplayer... at least i played all the time, levelled relatively fast. i generally dont like high end raids... sitting on your butt for extended periods of time is NOT fun. neither is doing pain in the ass epic quests. I was getting really tired of EQ. i was ready to quit my 60 ranger. <br>and then i met the person now known as Andlie. she was a druid on our old server, and i started liking EQ again just to play/talk with her.  we were both getting tired of the high end game on our server, and the politics...<br>then FV opened up, and here we are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  just her and I adventuring together, not much crappy politics to worry about or anything like that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and soon we get married on Luclin somewhere!!! that will be an event full of roleplaying!<br><br>btw, yes i am a guy roleplaying a lesbian female halfling... she wanted me to, and i thought it would be fun/funny as hell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><B>Veloxia Voluptuous <Clan Werre></B><BR>30 Halfling warrior<BR>"Me may be slow, but me spunkiness make up fer it!"<BR>*gnaws another enemy kneecap to shreds*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=le