r specialty. Myself and others mentioned what the true calling of a celric is especially in the chosing of Specialization skills and you didnt even know what the skills were for. I can't blame you for not roleplaying esp when you dont know what your class limits and uses are so I wont. In a world where BRELL would truely control your spell ability, the first time you grouped with an Ogre, created by Rallos - Brells enemy, you'd LOSE your casting ability as a Cleric. Stormwind is true neutral forced by Verant since all druids are this but I follow Tunare. To group with DEs or Ogres or Iksars is just ludicrous from a roleplay perspective so I dont do it. You made your bed, you chose your style of play and the need for gear or groups far over any roleplay sense and thats how you want it , fine no biggie. Still boggles me how you wanted to join Covenant of Truth a purely N/G aligned guild, note the GOOD in that, but didnt see how we would have issues of you grouping with evils or supporting dwarven killers or such beasts, which was fine by you. Either you dont know what roleplay is, you dont care or just dont care what other ppl's style of RP is. So be it brother, no sweat really. You made the choices and avoided all insight anyone suggested to you as truth or near truth and joined an N/E guild so dont expect us to aid you. Sorry but we as roleplayers of good, reguardless of the added alignment by Verant, dont help those who aid evils in any way ...... THATS ROLEPLAY, thanks  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarlithas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karlithas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/01 12:04:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> I don't get it.  Alot of people are talking how the TLC, language barrier, difficulty in finding groups in general ARE hampering the RP opportunities.  I want to know what do all these have to do with your capability to Roleplay?  Don't get me wrong, I am not accusing anybody here.  I am just curious to why people think these factors would affect the Roleplaying atmosphere in the game.<br><br>-Does TLC, Language barrier, and lack of grouping opportunities make FV a harder server to play and enjoy?<br><br>* Definitely a yes.  These rules make FV one of the hardest servers to play AND enjoy the entire game other than the PvP servers.<br><br>-Does TLC, language barrier, and lack of grouping makes people on FV unable to roleplay or lessen the RP opportunity?<br><br>* I don't know.  Does the server rules actually limit people's ability to interact in an IN-character fashion?  Does the server rules affects how a good aligned should react to an evil aligned?  Does the server rules demand how a dwarf should react at the sight of an ogre (taking into their racial history in consideration)?  <br>All the answers are NO.  It is the P-E-O-P-L-E that is responsible for that part, not the server rules.  <br><br>Hate FV for being a harder server and possible less enjoyment o the ENTIRE ASPECT of the game (but come on, let's face it, when is the last time we get to enjoy EVERYTHING in life?) , don't complain about FV limiting your so called &quot;RP&quot; capabilities.<br>It is you who determine what RP is and not server rules. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/01 6:11:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> Ok stormwind. I have 3 points, and I get this from www.everquest.com. Maybe you have some other source, maybe one you have written? But here is what the creators of the game have to say.<br><br>1. Brell and Veeshan are enemies. Not Brell plus good guys equal enemies of everything else.<br><br>2. Brell entered into pacts with Tunare , Prexus, Bristlebane and Cazic Thule.  He tried to convince Rallos Zek to side with him against Veeshan, but Rallos got kinda greedy and war ensued, which Rallos lost and was banished. Anyway when have you seen me be best buds with an Ogre? And past that, since Brell and Rallos aren't enemies now &lt;because it only says Brell and Veeshan are enemies&gt; what would stop me from befriending an Ogre, save his own pride from their defeat?<br><br>3. Brell is not a good guy. He is Neutral.<br><br>Why wouldn't you rez a troll? Brell and Cazic have a thing going. <br>When have you seen me group with Ogres? &lt;altho I have before, Oug comes to mind, you weren't there&gt;<br>I didn't click a button and choose evoc as my spec. I wasn't powerleveled by a consistant group of adventurers who let me sit around and heal all the time. I had to fight for what I have.<br><br>It isn't 'good and neutral' vs. evil. You make that up. That's your idealism. Mine says good vs. evil, fine. But I'm not good.<br><br>I'm neutral. Your druid is neutral, but you make up your own rules about how he sides with good and hates evil. Hey thats cool, your story has to fit somehow I guess.<br><br>So you go legitimize yourself and de-legitimize me. I don't see anything I do as non-rp. Hell I interract with people 50 levels lower than me, especially dwarves. There are more than a handful of people who knew or know me as Heagan the Hermit because of the length of time I went without choosing a guild. <br><br>And hey, like it or not, your guild isn't a strictly 'good' guild. You have neutral members which makes you a good and neutral guild. 'Oh but Heagan, I told you before, thats just game mechanics, our druids HAVE to be neutral'. Well thats your own argument turned on itself. You run to the EQ lore to say why I'm wrong, and in the process you are not only wrong but a rather verbal hypocrite.<br><br>KTHX <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/01 6:23:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Uhm thought this was a roleplay server...</span><hr size=1> Geez, another thing. You can't even be civil to the highest level Dwarf Paladin on the server. You have him on ignore because he offended you 35 levels ago by ks'ing your a_death_beetle or some such junk.<br><br>I tried to tell you that he is a good guy, just led a little astray by some problem players who dont play now, but you won't hear it. He tries to send you tells when he is Lfg, heck you know how hard it is when a good character is Lfg. But you ignore him.<br><br>Why don't you go ROLE PLAY with him for a bit and take him back with open arms? He doesn't have to prove anything to you imo. You're just a kewl d00d of a different brand. That doesn't make you better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugiordanaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GiordanaEQ</A>